Goals of this Project

We believe that the few Datasets that we do have,The New York times sentiment analysis, and the most influencial S&P 500 companies - Facebook, Amazon, Google, AMD, IBM and Tesla,are sufficient enough to help support our analysis. We are going to be using python libraries such as pandas, matplotlib, seaborn and jupyter labs as tools to help us complete this analysis.

Dataset 1: Sentiment Analysis of the New York Times

This Dataset contains values for over 30 years and multiple articles. The Data is filled with binary variables of multiple words usually associated with AI and technolgy such as - "Cyborg", "Singularity" and "Healthcare". These words and plenty others are placed into a negative or a positive column to judge the use of the word. Apart from these words we have columns with the article published date and time, paragraph and the section of the paper this was written under.

Dataset 2: S&P 500 historical data

This dataset contains multiple S&P 500 companies and their opening price, closing price, highest price and lowest price of the respective day. This dataset can help us see if even to a minor degree if the media can influence the stock market given that the stock market does seem to operate randomly. We do hope to see some relation if we're lucky.

Dataset 3: Exports and Imports

This dataset is the amount of money spent on imports and the value amount of exports in the United States. We will use it to see if an increase or decrease of either exports or imports affects the media's perception of new technological advancements and their behavior in the stock market.

Dataset 4: Amount invested in Research and Development

This dataset is the amount that the government put towards innovation of technological goods. We want to use this to see how it is affected by exports and imports. Then how less or more Research and Development affects innovation and people's perceptions towards AI.

Collaboration Plan:¶

Our goal is to answer our question, " How has AI in the media impacted technology stocks?"

The news plays a major role in shaping reader's persceptives. With AI becoming a popular area of discussion, authors have unitentionally displayed either their pestistimis or optism about AI. Is this bias affecting how readers are viewing technology companies ? In more depth, is the demand for stock in technology companies increasing or decraesing in accordance to media's
